B2B_sellin_client.name: B2B_sellin_client

B2B_sellin_fato.name: B2B_sellin_fato
B2B_sellin_fato.description: This sheet contains B2B sales data from BevCo Industries Inc., focusing on sell-in transactions. The data includes information about the period, client, product, operation type, volume, and revenue. Contains core transactional data.

columns.name: period_month_id
columns.description: Identifier for the month of the period in YYYYMM format

columns.name: period_id
columns.description: Identifier for the specific period, likely including day information in YYYYMMDD format

columns.name: operation_type
columns.description: Type of operation, indicating the nature of the transaction

columns.name: volume
columns.description: Volume of the product sold, possibly in liters or another unit

columns.name: billing
columns.description: Revenue generated from the sales, likely in the local currency

columns.name: insert_date
columns.description: Date and time when the data was inserted into the system

columns.name: folder_date
columns.description: Date representing the folder or batch date, likely in YYYYMM format

B2B_weather.name: B2B_weather
B2B_weather.description: Tracks weather data for various cities. It is a record of daily weather observations including temperature, precipitation, and humidity. The data is used for analyzing weather patterns and their impact on business operations, particularly in the context of B2B sales for BevCo Industries.

columns.name: order_date
columns.description: The date of the weather observation or order.

columns.name: uf
columns.description: The state abbreviation where the city is located.

columns.name: city
columns.description: The name of the city where the weather data was recorded.

columns.name: latitude
columns.description: The latitude coordinate of the city.

columns.name: longitude
columns.description: The longitude coordinate of the city.

columns.name: precipitation
columns.description: The amount of precipitation recorded on the order date, in millimeters.

columns.description: The average precipitation over the last 15 days, in millimeters.

columns.name: L365D_avg_precipitation
columns.description: The average precipitation over the last 365 days, in millimeters.

columns.name: avg_relativeHumidity
columns.description: The average relative humidity percentage on the order date.

columns.name: min_temperature
columns.description: The minimum temperature recorded on the order date, in degrees Celsius.

columns.name: max_temperature
columns.description: The maximum temperature recorded on the order date, in degrees Celsius.

columns.name: avg_temperature
columns.description: The average temperature on the order date, in degrees Celsius.

columns.description: The average temperature over the last 15 days, in degrees Celsius.

columns.name: L365D_avg_temperature
columns.description: The average temperature over the last 365 days, in degrees Celsius.

columns.name: min_temperatureFeelsLike
columns.description: The minimum 'feels like' temperature on the order date, in degrees Celsius.

columns.name: L365D_avg_temperatureFeelsLike
columns.description: The average 'feels like' temperature over the last 365 days, in degrees Celsius.

columns.name: data_capture
columns.description: The date when the data was last updated.

MKT_occasions.description: How often a specific soft drink brand is selected or consumed within a week over a four-week period, over different quarters from 2023 to 2024. It's a metric used to track brand popularity or consumption habits. P7D/P4W means 'Per 7 Days / Per 4 Weeks,' indicating the timeframe over which these occasions are measured.
